Push-Up Journey

Road to strong man.

This is a analysis on my Push-up journey where every time I completed a set of push-ups, I logged it with a Google survey and published it into a google spreadsheet.

data was collected over two weeks which are approximately one month apart where I had completed and logged 42 sets of push-ups. ## Does difficulty correlate to more reps? Ordered from lowest to highest median reps, it seems that at difficulty 4, I often did the most reps. The hardest difficulty median reps completed is actually in the middle significantly lower than difficulty 2. When we look at the variation however, difficulty 5 has much more variation compared to the others. This is largely due to the variant of pus-hup where the harder variants become much harder much quicker.

Have I improved over time?

Looking at all the data, it seems that yes, I have improved in the second week. The trend is much steeper with the alternative variants to the normal push up. This could be due to me getting used to the different variants where I get much better the more often I do it. But as you can see, the normal didnt improve that much. This sort of indicates to me that the amount you do for every variant over time is a bit of a log curve where you do a lot at when you first learn but after that you only get slightly better.

Looking a bit closer

Compared to the overall data, it seems that the last week, I had gotten worse? Looking at this data, we see that we actually got worse overtime in the last week. Data collection was actually going well at the start but during the week I had gotten sick so it became diffucult to complete more reps.

Does the hour of the day matter?

The data appears to not really have a trend where I was quite consistent with the amount push-ups completed at any time of the day. There doesnt seem to be any data to suggest that if I do push-ups in the morning vs afternoon, I would be able to rep more.

In Conclusion

From this experience, I was able to learn that I need to complete more push-ups. Its as simple as that, to get better at push-ups I just need to do more push-ups and with proper form, I can do even more.
